The most important lesson that our Ottoman past passed on to the Republic was the fact that the rapid perception of world conjuncture and change was an inevitable prerequisite for survival.
Since this lesson is so well assimilated, we have been able to be the exemplary country of this geography, which has managed to maintain its unity, integrity and stability in peace since the First World War.
